         <div type="commentary">
            <head>Commentary</head>
            <p/>
            <p>Probably 78 of the Actian era,
                    Phamenoth or Phamenouthi 23 = 19th March or 18th April, C.E. 48.</p>
            <p>Applebaum regards the child as Jewish. Her name alone is hardly sufficient
                    evidence, but seven-branched candlesticks have been recorded in this cemetery
                    and <ref type="inscription">A11600</ref> certainly contains Jewish names.</p>
            <p>This is the only epigraphic evidence for publicani at Apollonia; they may have
                    been concerned with public estates in the area, (see nos. <ref type="inscription">A04000</ref>,
                    <ref type="inscription">A08900</ref> and <ref type="inscription">A09000</ref>
                    for estates in the immediate neighborhood, at any
                    rate until the time of Vespasian<!-- , and IRC forthcoming for others at Ras el
                    Aslab, Ras el Hilal and Hanya, which might be conveniently administered from
                    Apollonia) -->, or with taxation, especially the collection of harbor-dues .</p>
         </div>
         
